Young Orson Wells. Put this in you collection. He plays the calculating Borgia to perfection.  But it is Everett Sloane as Mario Belli that is in my opinion the most interesting character and the best actor in the film.

I must have been 10 or 11 years old when I first remember seeing this movie.  There is one scene toward the end that I remembered even when I forgot the rest.  I just recently found this one and scared my wife to death when I was watching this and shouted &quot;I FOUND IT&quot;, when it got to this scene.  Can you guess the scene?

